ke, UK|year=2013|isbn=978-0-230-39222-9|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last=Goldberg|first=Philip|title=American Veda: From Emerson and the Beatles to Yoga and Meditation \u2013 How Indian Spirituality Changed the West|publisher=Harmony Books|location=New York, NY|year=2010|isbn=978-0-385-52134-5|url=https://archive.org/details/americanvedafrom00gold |url-access=registration|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Gould|first=Jonathan|year=2007|title=Can't Buy Me Love: The Beatles, Britain and America|title-link=Can't Buy Me Love (book)|publisher=Three Rivers Press|location=New York, NY|isbn=978-0-307-35338-2|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Greene|first=Doyle|year=2016|title=Rock, Counterculture and the Avant-Garde, 1966\u20131970: How the Beatles, Frank Zappa and the Velvet Underground Defined an Era|publisher=McFarland|location=Jefferson, NC|isbn=978-1-4766-6214-5|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Harris|first=John|authorlink=John Harris (critic)|year=2003|chapter=Cruel Britannia|title=Mojo Special Limited Edition: 1000 Days of Revolution (The Beatles' Final Years \u2013 Jan 1, 1968 to Sept 27, 1970)|location=London|publisher=Emap|pp=40\u201345|title-link=Mojo (magazine)#Special editions|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Harry |first=Bill |year=2000 |authorlink=Bill Harry | title = The Beatles Encyclopedia: Revised and Updated |publisher=Virgin |location=London |isbn=978-0-7535-0481-9 | ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book|last1=Hegarty|first1=Paul|last2=Halliwell|first2=Martin|title=Beyond and Before: Progressive Rock Since the 1960s|year=2011|publisher=The Continuum International Publishing Group|location=New York|isbn=978-0-8264-2332-0|authorlink1=Paul Hegarty (musician)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=taA2AqdCAJ0C|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Hertsgaard|first=Mark|authorlink=Mark Hertsgaard|title=A Day in the Life: The Music and Artistry of the Beatles|publisher=Pan Books|location=London|year=1996|isbn=0-330-33891-9|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Hodgson|first=Jay|year=2010|title=Understanding Records: A Field Guide to Recording Practice|publisher=Continuum|location=New York, NY|isbn=978-1-4411-5607-5|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first=Thom|last=Holmes|title=Electronic and Experimental Music: Technology, Music, and Culture ''(4th edn)''|year=2012|publisher=Routledge|location=New York, NY|isbn=978-0-415-89636-8|ref=harv|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/electronicexperi00holm}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Howard |first=David N. |year=2004 |title=Sonic Alchemy: Visionary Music Producers and Their Maverick Recordings |publisher=Hal Leonard Corporation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=y4Sk0FNXkjcC&pg=PA64&dq=rubber+soul+album+without+filler#v=onepage&q=rubber%20soul%20album%20without%20filler&f=false |isbn=978-0-634-05560-7 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Hunt|first=Ken|authorlink=Ken Hunt (music journalist)|chapter=India: East\u2013West Fusions|title=World Music: The Rough Guide (Volume 2: Latin and North America, Caribbean, India, Asia and Pacific)|year=2000|location=London|publisher=Rough Guides/Penguin|isbn=1-85828-636-0|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Ingham|first=Chris|title=The Rough Guide to the Beatles ''(2nd edn)''|year=2006|publisher=Rough Guides/Penguin|location=London|isbn=978-1-84836-525-4|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Inglis|first=Ian|year=2008|chapter=Cover Story: Magic, myth, and music|title= Sgt. Pepper and the Beatles: It Was Forty Years Ago Today|editor-last=Julien |editor-first=Olivier|publisher=Ashgate|isbn=978-0-7546-6708-7|chapter-url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=vZ-SB57WBo8C}}|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first=Ian|last=Inglis|chapter=Historical Approaches to Merseybeat|chapter-url= https://books.google.com/books?id=Zx_OpMptTFQC&pg=PA11#v=onepage&q&f=false|editor-last1=Leonard|editor-first1=Marion|editor-last2=Strachan|editor-first2=Robert|title=The Beat Goes On: Liverpool, Popular Music and the Changing City|publisher=Liverpool University Press|location=Liverpool, UK|year=2010|isbn=978-1-84631-190-1|ref=